en_115879_0	President Maithripala Sirisena said that although his journey for the future of the country is slow, it would never be reversed.
en_115879_1	The President stated this while addressing the 64 th anniversary commemoration of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party held at Rajarata Navodya sports ground at Kanduruwela in Polonnaruwa this afternoon.
en_115879_2	The anniversary held under the patronage of President Maithripala Sirisena were participated by the Maha Sangha, leaders of other religious denominations, former President Mahinda Rajapaksa, party ministers and MPs, party senior members, electoral organizers and party members.
en_115879_3	While delivering the welcome address, party General Secretary Duminda Dissanayake said that former President Chandrika Bandaranaike Kumaratunga was not present as she was out of the country.
en_115879_4	Later, SLFP General Secretary handed over a SLFP publication – Siri Laka newspaper and the 64 th anniversary souvenir to President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_115879_5	The key note address of the 64 th anniversary was delivered by the professor of the Sinhala unit of Colombo University Dr. Sarath Wijesuriya.
en_115879_6	During his speech, Professor Wijesuriya highlighted two occasions where Sri Lanka Freedom Party committed mistakes.
en_115879_7	Addressing the gathering, President Maithripala Sirisena stated despite changes that have taken place in politics within a year, it is a positive sign for all party members to throng around one platform.
en_115879_8	Expressing his views the president reiterated that political enmity should be eradicated for the benefit of the country. -------------------Update------------------------------------- Current President and the former get intimate – former lady President not yet reported The 64 th SLFP anniversary commemoration is currently taking place at Rajarata Navodaya Stadium in Kanduruwela, Polonnaruwa, under the patronage of President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_115879_9	This is the first Anniversary commemoration taking place in the party after the appointment of Maithripala Sirisena as Leader of SLFP as well as President.
en_115879_10	Many veterans in the party including the former President MP Mahinda Rajapaksa and former Prime Minister Dimu Jayaratne have also participated in the commemoration ceremony.
en_115879_11	However it is reported that former President Chandrika Bandaranaike Kumaratunga is still notably absent.
en_115879_12	Former President MP Mahinda Rajapaksa has also participated in the commemoration ceremony.
en_115879_13	Our correspondent stated that, Maha Sangha, priests of other religious groups, seniors of the party, Ministers and MPs, organizers, party members and a large number of people have attended the commemoration.
en_115879_14	(Pix by Roshan Thushara))
